-- Italtile of South Africa Says Wreckage Assumed to Be Company Plane Found
-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 2011-02-09T05:39:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-09/italtile-of-south-africa-says-wreckage-assumed-to-be-company-plane-found.html
  Italtile Ltd . said that wreckage
assumed to be the group’s company airplane was found in the
Robberg area near Plettenberg Bay on  South Africa ’s south coast.  Two crew and seven passengers were on board the flight,
which was travelling between Queenstown and Plettenberg Bay and
didn’t make it’s planned landing at 4:30 p.m. yesterday. Their
names won’t be released until their relatives have been
notified.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
